<!-- What is GEO Section -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-block">
            <h2>What is Generative Engine Optimisation?</h2>
            <p>Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO) addresses how content appears in AI-generated responses. As AI systems like ChatGPT, Google's AI overviews, and other LLM-powered tools become common information sources, businesses need strategies to be included in these generated responses.</p>
            <p>Unlike traditional search where users click through to websites, AI systems often synthesise answers from multiple sources. GEO focuses on making your content a source that AI systems reference and recommend.</p>
            <p>This is an emerging discipline that builds on traditional SEO principles while adapting to the specific behaviours of generative AI systems.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- How AI Search Works Section -->
<section class="content-section alt-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="content-block">
            <h2>How AI Search Systems Work</h2>
            <p>AI-powered search and recommendation systems operate differently from traditional search:</p>
            <ul class="content-list">
                <li><strong>Synthesis:</strong> AI systems combine information from multiple sources rather than simply ranking pages</li>
                <li><strong>Understanding:</strong> LLMs interpret meaning and context, not just keyword matching</li>
                <li><strong>Authority Assessment:</strong> AI systems evaluate source credibility based on training data and retrieval signals</li>
                <li><strong>Response Generation:</strong> Answers are constructed dynamically based on the query context</li>
            </ul>
            <p>These differences mean that content must be structured and positioned for AI comprehension and selection.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- GEO Principles Section -->
